        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 21 at 8:47PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>Low relative humidity values will combine with wind gusts of 25
to 35 mph and drying fuels to result in an increased danger of
fires burning out of control across Southeast West Virginia. This
is mainly where little to no rain or snow fell on Thursday.

These conditions could lead to the rapid spread of any fires that
do occur. Consult your local burn permitting authorities on
whether you may burn outdoors today. West Virginia law prohibits
burning in the spring from 7AM to 5PM...March 1st through May
31st.
</description>
